news.title: China's property sector stalked by Evergrande default fears
news.para: Weary Evergrande bondholders still haven't received almost $150 million worth of coupon payments that had been due on Monday, although there was little surprise after the firm had skipped two other payments in recent weeks.

news.title: Shriram Housing Finance gets Rs 300 crore equity capital from parent firm
news.para: ​The company has set a target of crossing Rs 5,600 crore of assets under management (AUM) target by March, as it had already crossed the Rs 4,000-crore mark in July and the new growth capital will help it expand the balance sheet faster.

news.title: China property association to examine difficulties faced by builders: Report
news.para: Tens of thousands of Chinese developers borrowed heavily to build homes during a red-hot property boom between 2016 and 2018, but are now facing a liquidity crunch amid sharply weaker demand and tighter regulations.

news.title: Spain to more than halve subsidy for firms specialised in renting out property
news.para: The discount on the company tax had previously favoured property rental firms over individual landlords - who receive 60% tax rebates for renting out their properties.

news.title: Puravankara to invest Rs 420 crore for two projects
news.para: ​The company on Wednesday launched two projects -- 'Provident Palm Vista' located near Shil Phata, Mumbai with one million square feet of saleable area and 'Tivoli Hills' located near Devanahalli, Bengaluru having a total saleable plot area of about 1.4 million square feet.

news.title: Cement production expected to be up 12% this fiscal: Report
news.para: "Based on the trends so far, ICRA expects the all-India cement production to report an increase by around 12 per cent to 332 million MT in 2021-22, which will be supported by the pent-up demand, rural housing demand and the pick-up in infrastructure activity.

news.title: Mohnish Pabrai's fund sold stake in Kolte-Patil Developers
news.para: In the case of Kolte-Patil Developers, Pabrai Investment Fund II owned 1,524,244 shares, or 2.01 per cent stake, in the Pune-based realtor as of June 30.

news.title: New land policy soon in Kerala: Industries minister
news.para: The policy is in its final shape and it is being introduced to simplify the procedures like transferring of ownership to the industrial unit managements.

news.title: Ex-servicemen yet to benefit from Pune civic body's property tax waiver scheme
news.para: Nearly 20,000 properties would receive tax waiver once the scheme is rolled out. The civic administration claimed that procedural formalities for the same were underway.

news.title: Nashik civic body to organise bike rallies to improve property tax collection
news.para: The revenue of NMC through property and water taxes has been badly affected due to the pandemic outbreak during the last 18 months.

news.title: Gujarat HC orders Ahmedabad civic body to inspect Vejalpur society
news.para: When the HC ordered the family last week to remove the construction, which cannot be regularised under GDCR rules, AMC officials insisted on the removal and the family approached the HC on Monday.

news.title: Ahmedabad: CBI registers case against six ASI and NMA officials
news.para: These officials had granted no objection certificates to a private company for constructions in the regulated or prohibited areas.

news.title: Vadodara: DBS Realty's chairman files cheating complaint against four directors
news.para: In his complaint, Sanjay Shah, chairman of DBS Realty Pvt Ltd, told the police that he decided to launch a project at Kamlapura village in Waghodiya along with one of the accused Kamlesh Shah, who was an administrator of a large parcel of land owned jointly by 11 people, after the stakeholder evinced interest in the project.

news.title: Pune: Valuables worth Rs 7 lakh stolen from DS Kulkarni's bungalow
news.para: The developer has been in jail since his arrest in February 2018 in connection with an alleged Rs2,091 crore economic fraud case.

news.title: Gurugram civic body wants DLF 1, 2 & 3 handover by December 2021
news.para: On Tuesday, councillors of wards 34 and 35 and other civic body officials conducted a meeting with the representatives of DLF regarding the takeover of these colonies.
